Durban - KZN police have issued a warrant of arrest for  Lungisani Derrick Ndlovu who is alleged to have shot dead his relatives in Inanda in December. Ndlovu, 33, who is out on bail, failed to appear in the Ntuzuma Magistrate's Court on October 1. Ndlovu allegedly shot his Mbongiseni Zondo , 22, and Funani Zondo, 47, in Namibia, Inanda on December 27. According to police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, the suspect handed himself over to police and he was granted bail at Ntuzuma Magistrate's Court. "On 1 October 2018, he failed to appear before court and a warrant for his arrest was issued by the court," said Mbele. Detectives from Inanda SAPS are appealing to members of the community for assistance with regard of his whereabouts. Anyone with information is urged to contact D/Sergeant Mthethwa 072 259 3518/ 082 290 5726 or Crime stop on 08600 10111. Daily News 